5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105458016.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20WHO%20has%20requested%20detailed%20information%20from%20China%20regarding%20an%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%2C%20including%20undiagnosed%20pneumonia%20in%20children.%20China%20has%20been%20reporting%20a%20surge%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%2C%20with%20reports%20of%20long%20lines%20at%20pediatric%20hospitals%20and%20more%20severe%20cases%20than%20before.%20Chinese%20officials%20have%20attributed%20the%20illnesses%20to%20known%20pathogens%2C%20but%20some%20reports%20have%20described%20crowds%20of%20children%20with%20pneumonia%20without%20specifying%20the%20cause.%20The%20WHO%20has%20expressed%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20infections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fwho-asks-china-for-details-on-surge-of-respiratory-illness-in-kids%2Farticleshow%2F105458016.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20Says%20No%20%26quot%3BUnusual%26quot%3B%20Virus%20Behind%20Rising%20Pneumonia%20Cases%3A%20WHO%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EChina%20says%20no%20unusual%20or%20new%20pathogens%20have%20been%20detected%20in%20the%20upsurge%20in%20child%20respiratory%20illnesses%20in%20the%20north%2C%20the%20WHO%20said%20Thursday%20after%20pressing%20Beijing%20for%20detailed%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20mid-October%202023%2C%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20has%20been%20monitoring%20data%20from%20Chinese%20surveillance%20systems%20showing%20an%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illness%20in%20children%20in%20northern%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20health%20agency%20announced%20late%20Wednesday%20it%20had%20made%20an%20official%20request%20to%20Beijing%20for%20more%20data%2C%20but%20the%20government%20offered%20no%20public%20comment%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WHO%20said%20it%20held%20a%20teleconference%20on%20Thursday%20with%20the%20Chinese%20Center%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20and%20the%20Beijing%20Children's%20Hospital%2C%20facilitated%20by%20the%20National%20Health%20Commission%20and%20the%20National%20Administration%20of%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChinese%20authorities%20advised%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20detection%20of%20any%20unusual%20or%20novel%20pathogens%20or%20unusual%20clinical%20presentations%2C%20including%20in%20Beijing%20and%20Liaoning%2C%20but%20only%20the%20aforementioned%20general%20increase%20in%20respiratory%20illnesses%20due%20to%20multiple%20known%20pathogens%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20WHO%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20further%20stated%20that%20the%20rise%20in%20respiratory%20illness%20has%20not%20resulted%20in%20patient%20loads%20exceeding%20hospital%20capacities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWHO%20is%20closely%20monitoring%20the%20situation%20and%20is%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20national%20authorities%20in%20China.%20WHO%20will%20continue%20to%20provide%20updates%20as%20warranted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20organisation%20recommended%20that%20people%20in%20China%20follow%20measures%20to%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20respiratory%20illness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20include%20recommended%20vaccines%20against%20flu%2C%20Covid-19%20and%20other%20respiratory%20pathogens%3B%20keeping%20distance%20from%20people%20who%20are%20ill%3B%20staying%20home%20when%20ill%3B%20getting%20tested%20and%20medical%20care%20as%20needed%3B%20and%20wearing%20masks%20as%20appropriate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWHO%20does%20not%20recommend%20any%20specific%20measures%20for%20travellers%20to%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%20month%20marks%20the%20fourth%20anniversary%20since%20the%20outbreak%20of%20Covid-19%20in%20Wuhan%2C%20China%2C%20was%20first%20repor