d%20in%20making%20headlines%20for%20charges%20against%20him%20and%20his%20crypto%20exchange%2C%20which%20included%20breaching%20US%20anti-money-laundering%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcurrencies%2Fbinance-ceo-cz-guilty-plea-department-of-justice-money-laundering-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZhao%20pleaded%20guilty%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20left%20his%20role%20as%20CEO.%20Binance%20is%20set%20to%20pay%20over%20%244.3%20billion%20in%20fines%2C%20%2450%20million%20of%20which%20will%20be%20paid%20by%20the%20former%20CEO%20himself.%20A%20portion%20of%20that%20will%20go%20to%20settle%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20Commodity%20Futures%20Trading%20Commission%20for%20allowing%20US%20customers%20to%20trade%20unregistered%20crypto%20derivatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20statement%20made%20by%20CFTC%20Commissioner%20Christy%20Goldsmith%20Romero%20read%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20pirate%20ships%20in%20US%20markets%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Baccess%20to%20US%20customers%20is%20a%20privilege%2C%20not%20a%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldsmith%20added%20that%20the%20CFTC%20plans%20to%20continue%20its%20aggressive%20pursuit%20of%20crypto%20exchanges%20that%20violate%20trade%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20commissioner%20noted%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20tolerance%20for%20using%20VPNs%2C%20or%20any%20other%20actions%20that%20could%20circumvent%20KYC%20rules%2C%20including%20pop-up%20questions%20that%20merely%20ask%20users%20to%20attest%20that%20they%20aren't%20based%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20separate%20statement%2C%20CFTC%20Commissioner%20Caroline%20D.%20Pham%20said%20the%20CFTC's%20reach%20has%20no%20border.%20%26quot%3BIt%20should%20be%20crystal%20clear%20that%20the%20CFTC%20will%20not%20stop%20in%20its%20pursuit%20of%20non-U.S.%20entities%2C%26quot%3B%20Pham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20swift%20action%20comes%20amidst%20a%20prolonged%20case%20set%20against%20FTX-founder%20SBF%2C%20who%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20and%20was%20charged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjury-sam-bankman-fried-guilty-seven-counts-fraud-manhattan-trial-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewith%20seven%20felony%20counts%2C%20including%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20money%20laundering%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20remains%20at%20New%20York's%20Metropolitan%20Detention%20Center%20awaiting%20his%20sentencing%3Cs%3E.%3C%2Fs%3E%20He%20could%20face%20up%20to%20110%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcftc-aggressive-binance-case-is-a-warning-to-all-violators-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700778153000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655fbba99c7d23cb3b9f41cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcftc-aggressive-binance-case-is-a-warning-to-all-violators-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CFTC%20Commissioner%20says%20there%20are%20%26quot%3Bno%20pirate%20ships%26quot%3B%20in%20US%20markets.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcftc-aggressive-binance-case-is-a-warning-to-all-violators-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20illegally%20denied%20benefits%20to%20the%20first%20unionized%20store%20in%20the%20country%2C%20says%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Apple%20store%20employee%20with%20customers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F643ed8210a29b40018810c89%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EOctavio%20Jones%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EApple%20improved%20its%20benefits%20to%20Apple%20Store%20employees%20nationwide%20last%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20June%202022%2C%20the%20Towson%20Apple%20Store%20became%20the%20first%20Apple%20Store%20in%20the%20country%20to%20unionize%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20NLRB%20and%20the%20Towson%20union%20allege%20that%20Apple%20illegally%20denied%20these%20benefits%20to%20unionized%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board%20filed%20a%20complaint%20against%20Apple%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20company%20violated%20US%20labor%20law%20by%20withholding%20benefits%20from%20unionized%20workers%20at%20its%20Towson%2C%20Maryland%2C%20store%2C%20which%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebaltimorebanner.com%2Feconomy%2Fbusinesses%2Fapple-union-towson-contract-QOPQJ243YZEFJL3XHIVSAWK7UE%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Towson%2520store%2520became%2520the%2Cget%2520through%2520the%2520holiday%2520season.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethe%20first%20Apple%20Store%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20country%20to%20unionize%20in%20June%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NLRB%20complaint%20comes%20about%20a%20year%20after%20the%20International%20Association%20of%20Machinists%20and%20Aerospace%20Workers%20(IAM)%2C%20which%20represents%20the%20Towson%20workers%2C%20filed%20its%20own%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20initial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nlrb.gov%2Fcase%2F05-CA-306442%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EIAM%20complaint%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20filed%20November%202%2C%202022%2C%20alleges%20that%20Apple%20improved%20its%20health%20and%20education%20benefits%20for%20Apple%20Store%20workers%20nationwide%20the%20month%20prior%20but%20excluded%20the%20unionized%20Towson%20workers%20from%20the%20improvements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NLRB%20and%20the%20IAM%20both%20claim%20that%20Apple's%20motivation%20was%20the%20assistance%20unionized%20employees%20provided%20to%20other%20Apple%20Store%20workers%20attempting%20to%20unionize.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKayla%20Blado%2C%20press%20secretary%20for%20the%20NLRB%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20press%20release%20that%20the%20complaint%20does%20not%20represent%20a%20final%20NLRB%20decision.%20Rather%2C%20it's%20the%20first%20step%20that%20enables%20its%20Regional%20Office%20to%20investigate%20the%20claims%20and%20seek%20a%20settlement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20parties%20don't%20settle%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20hearing%20with%20an%20NLRB%20Administrative%20Law%20Judge%20(ALJ)%20beginning%20February%2020%2C%202024%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20ALJ's%20decision%20can%20then%20be%20appealed%20to%20the%20Board%20and%20then%20to%20federal%20appeals%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Apple%2C%20the%20Towson%20Apple%20union%2C%20and%20the%20NLRB%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-illegally-denied-benefits-unionized-workers-claims-nlrb-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700777556000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655fc4999c7d23cb3b9f424b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-illegally-denied-benefits-unionized-workers-claims-nlrb-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apple%20illegally%20withheld%20benefits%20from%20the%20first%20unionized%20Apple%20Store%20in%20the%20country%2C%20claims%20NLRB.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22chaskins%40insider.com%20(Caroline%20Haskins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-illegally-denied-benefits-unionized-workers-claims-nlrb-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98The%20Witcher%E2%80%99%20Author%20Laughs%20Off%20Netflix%20%E2%80%98Never%20Listening%E2%80%99%