mains%20to%20the%20south%20pole%20of%20the%20lunar%20surface.%20The%20company%20charges%20%2412%2C500%20for%20a%20one-way%20trip%20to%20the%20moon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F07%2Fmagazine%2Fspace-burial.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Celestis%20has%20launched%2017%20of%20these%20so-called%20memorial%20spaceflights%20since%201994.%20Some%20will%20rocket%20straight%20up%20and%20descend%3B%20some%20will%20orbit%20Earth%3B%20some%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20moon%3B%20and%20some%20will%20simply%20hurtle%20into%20space%20and%20keep%20on%20going.%20Celestis%20sends%20its%20cargo%20on%20spacecraft%20undertaking%20unrelated%20scientific%20and%20commercial%20missions.%20Packages%20start%20at%20around%20%242%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Ohm's%20real%20reason%20for%20sending%20his%20DNA%20to%20the%20moon%20is%20practical%3A%20in%20case%2C%2030%2C000%20or%2040%2C000%20years%20from%20now%2C%20some%20remnant%20of%20this%20civilization%20or%20another%20civilization%20altogether%20discovers%20his%20genetic%20blueprints%2C%20and%E2%80%94what%2C%20exactly%3F%20Anything%2C%20really!%20But%20if%20they're%20sophisticated%20enough%20to%20find%20his%20DNA%20and%20utilize%20it%2C%20Ohm%20presumes%20it%20would%20be%20for%20something%20extremely%20cool%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ENYT.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700749140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2F8stcq0vo_ken-ohm_625x300_23_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fus-professor-wants-to-send-his-dna-to-the-moon-and-hopes-to-be-cloned-by-aliens-4600466%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20physics%20professor%20harbours%20ambitious%20plans%20for%20his%20DNA%20after%20his%20death%3B%20he%20envisions%20sending%20it%20to%20the%20moon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F