20trapped%20workers%20through%20a%20four-inch%20pipe%2C%20their%20diet%20stayed%20suboptimal%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdehradun%2Fbleak-tunnel-vision-trapped-workers-stare-at-health-crisis%2Farticleshow%2F105320669.cms%5C%22%3Ed%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdehradun%2Fbleak-tunnel-vision-trapped-workers-stare-at-health-crisis%2Farticleshow%2F105320669.cms%5C%22%3Ery%20fruits%2C%20puffed%20rice%20and%20popcorn%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20after%20nine%20days%2C%20when%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkhichdi-in-bottles-1st-hot-meal-for-trapped-uttarakhand-tunnel-workers-in-9-days-4590699%5C%22%3Esix-inch%20pipe%20was%20eventually%20pushed%20through%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20workers%2C%20did%20they%20get%20their%20first%20cooked%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20lack%20of%20preparation%20drew%20flak%20from%20Jharkhand%20chief%20minister%20Hemant%20Soren.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20commencing%20work%20on%20such%20projects%2C%20one%20needs%20to%20have%20safety%20protocols%20in%20place%20and%20also%20have%20rescue%20plans%20in%20case%20of%20emergencies%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Fjharkhand%2Fhemant-soren-slams-central-government-over-tunnel-mishap-in-uttarkashi%2Fcid%2F1981922%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20the%20situation%20is%20that%20even%20after%20so%20many%20days%2C%20there%20are%20talks%20of%20hiring%20foreign%20experts%20for%20rescue%20works.%20We%20have%20no%20option%20but%20to%20wait.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20asked%20Navayuga%20why%20the%20escape%20tunnel%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20been%20built%2C%20if%20it%20had%20used%20explosives%2C%20and%20why%20it%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20planned%20for%20contingencies%20despite%20multiple%20warnings%20about%20the%20Himalayas%20being%20fragile%20and%20unstable.%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20it%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20questions%2C%20however%2C%20scratch%20the%20surface.%20Silkyara%20(and%20Teesta%20III)%20are%20proverbial%20canaries%20in%20a%20mine%2C%20giving%20us%20a%20deeper%20warning%20than%20just%20the%20specific%20infirmities%20of%20these%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-sikkim-cm-cannot-evade-responsibility-on-the-teesta-dam-breach%5C%22%3EThe%20Sikkim%20CM%20Cannot%20Evade%20Responsibility%20on%20the%20Teesta%20Dam%20Breach%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20ceded%20landscape%20of%20environmental%20protections%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20night%20of%20May%206%2C%202020%2C%20history%20repeated%20itself%20in%20Vizag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%203%20am%20that%20night%2C%20a%20neuro-toxic%20gas%20leaked%20from%20a%20chemical%20plant%20of%20LG%20Polymers%20and%20spread%20into%20the%20colonies%20abutting%20the%20plant.%20Thirty-six%20years%20after%20the%20Bhopal%20Gas%20Tragedy%2C%20Indians%20again%20woke%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fvizag-factory-chemical-gas-leak-victim-account-recounts-horror-breathlessness-burning-eyes%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20breath%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fvizag-factory-chemical-gas-leak-victim-account-recounts-horror-breathlessness-burning-eyes%5C%22%3Ee%2C%20their%20eyes%20b%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fvizag-factory-chemical-gas-leak-victim-account-recounts-horror-breathlessness-burning-eyes%5C%22%3Eurning%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20least%2011%20people%20died%20in%20the%20incident.%20About%205%2C000%20were%20hospitalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20days%20that%20followed%2C%20it%20emerged%20that%20the%20plant%20had%20been%20running%20without%20an%20environmental%20clearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20sobering%20moment.%20After%20the%20Bhopal%20Gas%20Tragedy%2C%20India%20passed%20new%20laws%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Flegislative.gov.in%2Factsofparliamentfromtheyear%2Fenvironment-protection-act-1986%5C%22%3EEnvironment%20Protection%20Act%20(EPA)%2C%201986%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Flegislative.gov.in%2Factsofparliamentfromtheyear%2Fpublic-liability-insurance-act-1991%5C%22%3EPublic%20Liability%20Insurance%20Act%20(PLIA)%2C%201991%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20amended%20existing%20ones%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Flegislative.gov.in%2Factsofparliamentfromtheyear%2Ffactories-act-1948%5C%22%3EFactories%20Act%2C%201948%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20public%20costs%20of%20industries%20working%20with%20hazardous%20technologies%20and%20chemicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20these%20laws%20too%20were%20weakened%20repeatedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20night%20in%20Vizag%2C%20the%20full%20scale%20of%20usurped%20environmental%20protections%20became%20suddenly%20visible.%20As%20%3Cem%3EArticle-14%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.article-14.com%2Fpost%2Findia-is-back-to-a-time-before-the-bhopal-gas-tragedy%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20a%20poisonous%20gas%20leaks%20from%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fgross-negligence-lack-of-training-caused-vizag-gas-leak-report-1683735-2020-05-30%5C%22%3Epoorly%20maintained%3C%2Fa%3E%20industrial%20unit%2C%20operating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2020%2F05%2Fyears-of-neglect-led-to-vizag-gas-tragedy%2F%5C%22%3Ewithout%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20environmental%20clearance%2C%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20residential%20neighbourhoods%2C%20it%20invites%20more%20than%20comparisons%20with%20Union%20Carbide.%20It%20forces%20the%20belated%20recognition%20that%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20effective%20protection%20against%20industrial%20pollution%2C%20India%20is%20back%20where%20she%20was%20before%20the%20Bhopal%20Gas%20Tragedy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F07103316%2F2020_5img07_May_2020_PTI07-05-2020_000012B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F07103316%2F2020_5img07_May_2020_PTI07-05-2020_000012B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F07103316%2F2020_5img07_May_2020_PTI07-05-2020_000012B-300x196.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F07103316%2F2020_5img07_May_2020_PTI07-05-2020_000012B-1024x667.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-453117%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22782%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPeople%20being%20treated%20at%20a%20hospital%20after%20a%20major%20chemical%20gas%20leakage%20at%20LG%20Polymers%20industry%20in%20RR%20Venkatapuram%20village%2C%20Visakhapatnam%2C%20Thursday%2C%20May%2007%2C%202020.%20Photo%3A%20Videograb%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20big%20warning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20the%20big%20lesson%20from%20Silkyara%20and%20Teesta%20III%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20time%2C%20seeking%20to%20protect%20places%20like%20Silent%20Valley%2C%20India%20created%20a%20strong%20environmental%20governance%20architecture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%20however%2C%20a%20double%20movement%20has%20played%20out.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20the%20country%20rolled%20out%20large%20infrastructure-building%20drives%20%E2%80%93%20to%20set%20up%20thermal%20power%20projects%2C%20erect%20dams%2C%20build%20highways%2C%20set%20up%20ports.%20In%20tandem%2C%20given%20industrial%20lobbying%20for%20deregulation%20and%20the%20gravy%20train%20around%20infrastructure-building%2C%20the%20country%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.article-14.com%2Fpost%2Findia-is-back-to-a-time-before-the-bhopal-gas-tragedy%5C%22%3Eweakened%20its%20environmental%20governance%20architecture%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20a%20cynical%20game.%20For%20over%2020%20years%2C%20the%20environment%20ministry%20has%20been%20presented%20as%20a%20roadblock%2C%20delaying%20the%20construction%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20industrial%20plants%20and%20infrastructure%20projects.%20The%20ministry%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fcompany%2Fcorporate-trends%2Findia-inc-unhappy-over-delays-in-green-nods-by-environment-minister-jayanthi-natarajan%2Farticleshow%2F18438096.cms%5C%22%3Ewas%20also%20presented%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fed-attaches-15-properties-of-a-raja-under-pmla-act%2Farticle67404846.ece%5C%22%3Eas%20corrupt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20successive%20ministers%20taking%20bribes%20to%20clear%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20fix%20these%20problems%2C%20the%20country%20needed%20to%20insulate%20project%20approvals%20from%20inefficiency%20and%20political%20interference.%20One%20solution%20was%20to%20create%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fpolicy%2Fenvironment-clearance-as-patronage%2Farticleshow%2Fmsid-5434996%2Ccurpg-2.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ea%20statutory%20environment%20regulator%20like%20America%E2%80%99s%20Environment%20Protection%20Agency%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20would%20also%20do%20away%20with%20politicians%E2%80%99%20power%20to%20issue%20environment%2Fforest%20clearances.%20This%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen.%20Instead%2C%20successive%20governments%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.article-14.com%2Fpost%2Findia-is-back-to-a-time-before-the-bhopal-gas-tragedy%5C%22%3Eweakened%20India%E2%80%99s%20environmental%20clearance%20process%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Public%20hearings%20were%20defanged%3B%20project%20proponents%20were%20allowed%20to%20define%20the%20environmental%20parameters%20along%20which%20their%20projects%20would%20be%20evaluated%3B%20the%20time%20taken%20to%20evaluate%20projects%20was%20slashed%3B%20one%20could%20go%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chickens%20are%20now%20coming%20home%20to%20roost.%20In%20both%20Teesta%20III%20and%20Silkyara%2C%20policy%20plans%20and%20project%20reports%20barely%20acknowledged%20environmental%20risks.%20In%20the%20first%20instance%2C%20the%20environmental%20impact%20assessment%20was%20cursory.%20In%20the%20second%2C%20there%20was%20no%20environmental%20impact%20assessment%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20both%20cases%2C%20geological%20risks%20showed%20up%20during%20construction.%20All%20of%20this%20raises%20a%20large%20question.%20Over%20the%20last%20nine%20years%2C%20the%20NDA%20has%20embarked%20on%20a%20new%20double%20movement%20of%20fresh%20infrastructure%20projects%20(river-interlinking%2C%20inland%20waterways%2C%20more%20highways%E2%80%A6)%20while%20continuing%20to%20weaken%20India%E2%80%99s%20environmental%20laws.%20The%20resulting%20interplay%20%E2%80%93%20between%20disregarded%20environmental%20risks%20and%20infrastructure%20projects%20%E2%80%93%20has%20to%20be%20better%20understood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tragedy%20here%20is%20that%20the%20resulting%20costs%20are%20unfairly%20distributed.%20At%20Silkyara%2C%2041%20workers%20came%20close%20to%20losing%20their%20lives.%20In%20the%20days%20after%20Teesta%20III%E2%80%99s%20collapse%2C%20social%20media%20was%20filled%20with%20images%20of%20locals%20trying%20to%20save%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%2C%20however%2C%20are%20highly%20visible%20instances%20of%20planning%20failures.%20Others%20are%20more%20invisible.%20Poorly%20scrutinised%20risks%20result%20in%20cost-%20and%20time%20overruns%2C%20turning%20projects%20unviable%2C%20even%20forcing%20states%20to%20support%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20are%20the%20costs%20of%20looking%20at%20environmental%20protections%20as%20barriers%20for%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EM.%20Rajshekhar%20is%20an%20independent%20reporter%20studying%20corruption%2C%20oligarchy%2C%20and%20the%20political%20economy%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%3Cem%3Es%20environment.%20He%20is%20also%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FDespite-State-India-Lets-People%2Fdp%2F8194879019%2F%5C%22%3EDespite%20the%20State%3A%20Why%20India%20Lets%20Its%20People%20Down%20and%20How%20They%20Cope%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700742644000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20225721%2FF_TZ16gaYAARVxR.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-collapse-warning-environment-development%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amidst%20relief%20that%20the%20trapped%20workers%20will%20soon%20be%20rescued%2C%20India%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20forget%20the%20key%20warning%20from%20the%20collapsed%20tunnel%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20environmental%20impact%20assessment%20system%20is%20broken.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-collapse-warning-environment-development%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Coal%20India%20to%20phase%20out%20mining%20equipment%20imports%20in%206%20years%2C%20says%20govt%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700742258000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2022-11%2F25%2Ffull%2F1669362087-5275.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fcoal-india-to-phase-out-mining-equipment-imports-in-6-years-says-govt-123112300699_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22To%20curb%20these%20imports%20and%20boost%20domestic%20manufacturing%2C%20CIL%20has%20devise